# Copy to `.env` in project root (or cwd). Never commit `.env`.
#
# =============================================================================
# RUNBOOK — Polymarket live BUY (Tyrex + official docs)
# =============================================================================
#
# Polymarket splits THREE unrelated credential planes (do not mix them up):
#
#  (1) CLOB L2  — apiKey + secret + passphrase  →  5 `POLY_*` HMAC headers on
#      trading REST (`/order`, `/balance-allowance`, etc.).
#      Source: https://docs.polymarket.com/developers/CLOB/authentication
#
#  (2) Relayer  — gasless `WALLET-CREATE` / `WALLET` batches (deposit wallet).
#      Auth: Builder API HMAC (`POLY_BUILDER_*` headers) OR `RELAYER_API_KEY` +
#      `RELAYER_API_KEY_ADDRESS`. Independent from CLOB L2 keys.
#      Source: https://docs.polymarket.com/api-reference/relayer
#           + https://docs.polymarket.com/developers/builders/relayer-client
#
#  (3) Order signing — private key + `signature_type` + `funder` inside
#      `py-clob-client-v2`. For NEW deposit-wallet accounts Polymarket documents:
#      `signature_type = 3` (POLY_1271), `funder` = deposit wallet; deploy wallet,
#      fund pUSD ON THAT ADDRESS, approve spenders via relayer `WALLET` batch,
#      then `balance-allowance/update` with `signature_type=3`.
#      Source: https://docs.polymarket.com/trading/deposit-wallets
#
# Tyrex env precedence (same keys — TYREX_* WINS if set; do not leave stale TYREX_*):
#   `TYREX_PRIVATE_KEY`  >  `POLYMARKET_PK`
#   `TYREX_SIGNATURE_TYPE`  >  `POLYMARKET_SIGNATURE_TYPE`  (default "0" if both unset)
#   `TYREX_FUNDER`  >  `POLYMARKET_FUNDER`
#   Source: `src/tyrex_pm/venue/polymarket/clob_env.py` → `try_create_clob_client()`
#
# Correct deposit-wallet path (checklist):
#
#   [ ] A. One MetaMask / signing EOA: put private key in `POLYMARKET_PK` (or
#           `TYREX_PRIVATE_KEY`). Do not also set the other to a different key.
#
#   [ ] B. `POLYMARKET_SIGNATURE_TYPE=3` (and unless intentional, leave
#           `TYREX_SIGNATURE_TYPE` UNSET so it does not override to 0 or 2).
#
#   [ ] C. `POLYMARKET_FUNDER` = Polymarket’s **deposit wallet** for that owner,
#           NOT the EOA. Confirm in UI: https://polymarket.com/settings
#           (“Invalid Funder” troubleshooting — auth doc).
#
#   [ ] D. CLOB API credentials were created **with the same key as (A)**:
#           either UNSET `POLYMARKET_API_*` so `try_create_clob_client()` calls
#           `create_or_derive_api_key()`, OR set all three from derivation using
#           `scripts/generate_clob_api_creds.py` with that same PK.
#           Mismatch → `/balance-allowance` can show 0 forever.
#
#   [ ] E. Relayer auth for deposit setup: `POLYMARKET_BUILDER_*` OR `RELAYER_API_*`,
#           plus `RELAYER_URL=https://relayer-v2.polymarket.com` (builders doc).
#
#   [ ] F. Deploy deposit wallet if needed (`WALLET-CREATE`), then run (no dry-run):
#           `python scripts/deposit_wallet_collateral_setup.py`
#           → pUSD `approve` batch + `balance-allowance/update` for sig=3.
#
#   [ ] G. Verify CLOB sees collateral:
#           `python scripts/deposit_wallet_collateral_setup.py --skip-batch --verbose`
#           Expect non-zero `balance` after (F); allowances huge after approvals.
#
#   [ ] H. Tyrex risk: default `config/risk/default.yaml` caps notional (`max_usd: 4`)
#           and Polymarket has venue min size (often 5 shares) — tiny `$` orders can
#           still fail locally; size BUY appropriately.
#
# Legacy fork (Polymarket “existing Safe / proxy” — NOT deposit-wallet flow):
#   `signature_type` = `1` or `2`, `funder` = that proxy/Safe address. Tyrex wiring
#   is the same (`try_create_clob_client`), but relayer steps differ; see auth doc
#   signature-type table: https://docs.polymarket.com/developers/CLOB/authentication
#
# =============================================================================

# --- (A) Signing key (one source of truth) ---
# TYREX_PRIVATE_KEY=
POLYMARKET_PK=

# --- (B/C) Wallet mode + funder (deposit wallet for type 3) ---
# Leave TYREX_SIGNATURE_TYPE unset unless you intentionally override POLYMARKET_* .
# TYREX_SIGNATURE_TYPE=
POLYMARKET_SIGNATURE_TYPE=3
# TYREX_FUNDER=
POLYMARKET_FUNDER=

# --- CLOB host / chain ---
TYREX_CLOB_HOST=https://clob.polymarket.com
TYREX_CHAIN_ID=137

# --- (D) CLOB L2 API credentials (derive from same PK as POLYMARKET_PK if unsure) ---
POLYMARKET_API_KEY=
POLYMARKET_API_SECRET=
POLYMARKET_PASSPHRASE=

# --- Optional: order-builder attribution (Tyrex → py-clob `BuilderConfig`; NOT relayer auth) ---
# TYREX_BUILDER_CODE=
# TYREX_BUILDER_ADDRESS=

# --- Heartbeats ---
# TYREX_HEARTBEAT_ID=
# POLYMARKET_HEARTBEAT_ID=

# --- (E/F) Relayer (deposit-wallet WALLET batches + `/submit`) ---
RELAYER_URL=https://relayer-v2.polymarket.com
POLYMARKET_BUILDER_API_KEY=
POLYMARKET_BUILDER_SECRET=
POLYMARKET_BUILDER_PASSPHRASE=
# Or Relayer API key pair (alternative to Builder HMAC):
# RELAYER_API_KEY=
# RELAYER_API_KEY_ADDRESS=

# --- Tyrex supervisor tuning (optional) ---
# TYREX_SUBMIT_GRACE_S=15
# TYREX_PROVISIONAL_UNKNOWN_TERMINAL_TIMEOUT_S=60
# TYREX_VENUE_CONFIRM_GRACE_S=15
# TYREX_VENUE_CONFIRM_PROVISIONAL_TIMEOUT_S=60
# TYREX_ADOPTION_GRACE_S=5
# TYREX_USER_WS_DISABLE=1   # only if WebSocket blocked; use scenario require_user_ws_live: false
